  <div slot="about" class="editorial-content">
    <h2>YouTube Keyword Density Checker: Optimize Video Description Metadata</h2>
    <div style="margin: 1.5rem 0; background: var(--color-bg-alt); padding: 1.25rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-brand);">
      <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5;">
        🔍 <strong>Looking for high-volume keywords to target?</strong> Use our free <a href="/tools/youtube-keyword-generator" style="color: var(--color-brand); text-decoration: underline;">YouTube Keyword Generator</a> to discover search intent terms and volume metrics.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>
      In YouTube SEO, video descriptions play a central role in helping YouTube's search crawler understand the context of your content. When viewers search for specific tutorials, reviews, or guides, YouTube evaluates how frequently target keywords and semantic terms appear within your description text. However, there is a fine line between strategic keyword inclusion and unnatural keyword stuffing. Exceeding recommended keyword repetition limits can trigger algorithm spam filters and hurt your channel's search rankings. Our free <strong>YouTube keyword density checker</strong> allows creators to analyze description word counts, calculate 1 to 3-word phrase frequency percentages, and audit spam risk levels in real-time.
    </p>

    <h3>How to Use This Tool</h3>
    <p>
      Auditing your YouTube description metadata with our interactive tool is straightforward. Follow these steps:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Paste Description Text:</strong> Copy and paste your video description or script text into the main text area input.</li>
      <li><strong>Target Keyword:</strong> Enter your primary target keyword or phrase (e.g. gaming PC).</li>
      <li><strong>Analysis Settings:</strong> Toggle options to exclude common English stop words or ignore words under 3 characters.</li>
      <li><strong>Analyze Density:</strong> Click <strong>Analyze Density</strong> to run the audit.</li>
      <li><strong>Review Breakdown:</strong> Review your Total Word Count, Target Keyword Density percentage, Spam Risk Level, and 1 to 3-word phrase tables.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>What is YouTube Keyword Density</h3>
    <p>
      <strong>YouTube keyword density</strong> is the percentage measurement of how many times a specific keyword or phrase appears inside your video description relative to the total number of words in that description text.
    </p>
    <p>
      Maintaining a healthy keyword density ensures your metadata stays optimized while complying with YouTube's search policies:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Ideal Safe Density (1% – 3%):</strong> The sweet spot for video SEO. Your target keyword appears naturally 2 to 4 times in a 250-word description, signaling strong topic relevancy.</li>
      <li><strong>Moderate Risk (3% – 5%):</strong> Approaching over-optimization. Consider replacing repetitive keywords with LSI (Latent Semantic Indexing) synonyms.</li>
      <li><strong>High Spam Risk (> 5%):</strong> Triggers keyword stuffing flags. YouTube may penalize videos that repeat keywords excessively. Before publishing, check your overall title limits using our <a href="/tools/youtube-title-length-checker">YouTube Title Length Checker</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How Does It Work?</h3>
    <p>
      The checker processes your text using multi-word tokenization algorithms:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Word Tokenization:</strong> Cleans punctuation, handles case sensitivity, and splits text into individual words.</li>
      <li><strong>N-Gram Phrase Extraction:</strong> Groups consecutive words into 2-word (bigrams) and 3-word (trigrams) phrases to detect exact multi-word search queries.</li>
      <li><strong>Density Percentage Calculation:</strong> Computes exact frequency ratios and compares target keyword occurrences against total word counts.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Example Calculation</h3>
    <p>
      Let us calculate the Keyword Density percentage for a sample YouTube video description:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Total Word Count ($W$):</strong> `300 words`<br />
      <strong>Target Keyword ($K$):</strong> `"gaming PC"`<br />
      <strong>Target Keyword Occurrences ($N$):</strong> `6 times`
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Formula:</strong><br />
      Keyword Density % = (Target Keyword Occurrences / Total Word Count) &times; 100
    </p>
    <p>
      Keyword Density % = (6 / 300) &times; 100 = 0.02 &times; 100 = <strong>2.0%</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      A keyword density of <strong>2.0%</strong> falls perfectly within YouTube's recommended 1% to 3% safe zone, ensuring optimal search indexing without triggering spam filters. You can also generate copy-paste tags for your upload with our <a href="/tools/youtube-tag-generator">YouTube Tag Generator</a>.
    </p>

    <h3>How To Use</h3>
    <p>
      Using our tool is intuitive. Paste your draft description into the input box, enter your target keyword, and click analyze. The live YouTube description mockup card updates automatically, highlighting target keyword occurrences in real-time so you can refine your phrasing before publishing.
    </p>

    <h3>Who Should Use This Tool?</h3>
    <p>
      This generator is designed for:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>YouTube Creators:</strong> Checking description drafts to avoid keyword stuffing before upload.</li>
      <li><strong>Video SEO Specialists:</strong> Auditing client channels and optimizing video metadata for higher search positions.</li>
      <li><strong>Copywriters & Content Managers:</strong> Ensuring video descriptions maintain natural readability and balanced keyword frequency.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

